reviews.text: Beautiful park. Very scenic and serene. My kids and I walked around admired the boats docked along the perimeter of the park. We saw seals and other marine life. Most of the time that would be enough, but I didn't see any playground for the kids. So if you bring your kids, bring your own toys and entertainment.

Marina Del Rey Christmas Boat Parade is why we went today. It is a very nice area for watching the boats decorated with Christmas lights, trees, inflatables, characters, elves, snowmen, carolers, etc. pass by as they loop around the Marina several times. This gives everyone an opportunity to find a good spot to take photographs. Parking was the hardest part of the evening because we arrived right at 6.p.m. when the show started. There were fireworks at 5:55 p.m. and  events throughout the day. I am definitely happy to have visited the Marina today.
Very quiet, weekdays and for (summer) non-special event weekends, moderate but still pleasant. One of my favorite hangouts in town!

Poor experience with the park  staff member Tiffany; we came today at 10.30 am to enjoy some picnic with kids. All tables empty- no reserved signs. I chose a random table and set up some fruit for kids and sandwiches. After 30 min a lady came up wearing regular clothes and without introducing herself said “you must pack up and leave within a minute”. I asked why and she said these tables are all reserved. I said  as no signs we did not know and we will move in a minute and asked for her name. She refused to give me her name and said “ lady, do you know what a minute means? “ I said 60 seconds and started packing up to move away from area. I did not want to cause a scene in front of kids. First- no signs posted, second: not asking nicely to move just “you must move”, third- rude attitude by park employee Tiffany . I went to the office to find out her name and she was frankly confrontational- no apology. I never refused to move and said nothing back to her. Most likely her attitude was due to us being immigrants with an accent. Oh well- rude rude rude. We have been going to this park forever but will just find a new spot.
I've been coming to this park for a long time in the marina , it has 360-degree views of the water and boats and my friend's got married their last week

Really nice path to walk..jog..cycle. exercise stations along the way are a bonus.
Was good. Ate some in n out.
Nice bike or jogging park with work out gear. No restroom, u may use it in library nearby.
Beautiful green space. Good for walking, running, and booking.

Pizza is good, but it's inconvenient when visiting. They are in an upscale neighborhood but do not accept credit nor debit cards only cash. That's usually how they do business in the ghetto. You have to download some app and pay on-line if you want to pay through alternate methods. They also accept company business checks, which people usually don't carry around when trying to get a quick bite to eat. Seems difficult to purchase a simple meal. Would be nice if they can consider convenience to customers.
$3.89 per slice and no combo deals. Tony’s pizza is 10 times better and half the price. Eat elsewhere, there is bound to be better food for similar price range. AVOID**

By far the worse experience I ever experienced in CALIFORNIA. A simple calzone arrived to my hotel oozing our ricotta cheese and the dough is wet. Doesn’t even look appetizing, asked them to have their driver pick it up and exchange for something else. They said no!! I have to speak to the owner. It’s 11pm at night and you can’t make a simple decision for good customer service. What a shame!! Will make sure I call the health department for this because raw dough is unacceptable as well.
Everything is pricey a can of coke was 3 bucks smh and the pizza is not that good.

Terrible, reheated old, pizza. It's 2019 and they only accept cash? Then their atm charges $2.50? So I end up paying $10 for one slice and a ranch? Ok. Take my money, but I'll never come back. Thanks.

Amazing food. Extensive wine options. Our waiter was very attentive and knew the wine options from top of his head! The stake is very very good.

The view is OK. Definitely don't go here for the view, unless you enjoy watching a lot of anchored boats.
It was very good. Good cocktails, food and presentation. Food is Ruth's Chris style, but warmer surroundings. Meaning, you can dress in jeans and a sweatshirt.

YUM! YUM! YUM! Went here on my way to the airport, not that it's anywhere near the airport, but it's on my way into the city :) This was a great meal. It looked so busy, but we were seated right away. Waiter had great suggestions, kept our waters full and was very friendly. Definitely recommend, anything on the menu is going to be good, I promise!

This was one of the worst chart house as I’ve ever been to. The staff was so not organized. The salad bar head look like it been sitting in the warmth of the sun. It was missing many dishes. I’ve been to many fancy restaurants in my life. And I know the chart houses have been a pretty solid chain. This chart house however was filled with misery. I would not ever recommend eating here.
Great food. Ton of delicious fish options. The staff k ows the cuisine very well. Highly recommended.
It was good.. reasonably priced. Not the best or fanciest, not sugar fish or even Hama caliber.. but very reasonably priced.
Delicious and authentic. My impression is a little cultural sensitivity goes a long way. The staff are absolute professionals. I will go here again. Very good.

Food was good, a little on the expensive side for the quantity. Service was the slowest ever, close to an hour and a half to bring the food to four of our six-person group, while two of us were served within minutes! Food arrived the moment we were ready to get up and leave. Something went really wrong and they did not even explain, or at least warn us it will take a long time.
Bad service, bad rolls and over priced. The sushi was good but not worth the rest. With so many other options, go somewhere else.

Bland food, slow service, and incorrect orders. No hostess at the front, makes it awkward to be seated.  Atmosphere was alright, but food quality was the real let down. Tried the Tonkotsu ramen, several rolls, teriyaki beef, and salad. Bland at best, gross at worst.

The wine, dessert, appetizer plate and company of friends were great. I am a Foodie the Veal with the split Asparagus spear with  too much cheese covering it was not to liking. Thank God for the company of friends. Great place for a date at sunset..

I stop by to check the restaurant out and use the bathroom. I was coming back the next day and wanted to eat there. While I was in the bathroom the owner started to hit the door so hard I thought it was going fall in. When I came out of the bathroom he just started to scream at me because I was using his bathroom. I am a business man and I am not some homeless person and he didn’t ask me I wanted to to be seated just told me leave. I have not been so insulted in my life. I was going to have dinner there this week I guess not now. 
I am disable now and it is very painful for me to get around when he treated me that way it broke my heart. It very said when people think they are better than the rest of us. I will pray that God will help man learn that he not better than the rest of us and life is to short to treat people that way. Maybe he doesn’t now the Golden Rule treat others the way he wants to be treated.
Went there for a quick lunch, but stayed for over two hours. Loved the view and the food.
The menu was non negotiable, very lousy Italian selection for the price and atmosphere. All very similar options and they are piss poor
Good food and service,  great value

I traveled to California from Texas with a few friends and we wanted to try food that wasn’t in found in Texas. Tony P’s was amazingggggg! I had the Alfredo and was very pleased. Our server was really cool and chilled and made us feel really comfortable. Only thing that shocked us were the fact that birds were flying around while we were eating. They didn’t bother us though, so I guess it wasn’t a problem. Definitely recommend them.

4 stars for ambience and location, 3 stars for food, 2 stars for price.
We had family brunch celebrating a birthday. I had shrimp, my husband had steak.
They were ok. I can find much better food in LA for the price, but I suppose we were paying for the ambience. Would not recommend.

Great neighborhood restaurant and sports bar!  If you are looking for a fun place to watch a game this is your spot.  Tons of great beers on tap with a friendly staff.  Patio has great views of the marina as well.  Cheers!

We went on a Friday evening and I ordered the all you can eat fish, which is a Friday special. The fish is all you can eat because it's so heavily breaded. I didn't care for it.  It should be called all you can eat bread. Very disappointing. Usually I don't like shoestring french fries, but I did like theirs. Wish I had gone elsewhere.

It was awesome. The waiter that attended us was so nice. He was so attentive to our needs and even recommended some dishes. He explained in detail what they had adding some historic background to one of the drinks. I would definitely go back again. The view there is also nice overlooking the boating docks if you sit by the patio. And parking is free!!

Great establishment with a great view.  We had American style dishes that were freshly prepared with great table side presentation. Quality was excellent and all of the right taste buds participated and were excited.  This is a well reviewed place so I will only add couple of highlights. Dining room staff was excellent with attentive service and timely table visits.  So why only 4 stars?   To be fair maybe it was timing. We arrived just 2 minutes before they officially open for lunch. However the hostess completely  ignored us for about 5 minutes while being preoccupied on her cell phone. Then there was unnecessary additional 5 min at the bar while we waited to be seated in what appeared to be empty restaurant.   Outside of the hostess greeting issue this could have been a 5 star review.

We went there for lunch to celebrate our anniversary and I can't be happier with the choice. Service was fantastic! The owner, Craig I think, was so thoughtful and accommodating. We got a table at the window with the boats view and offered a free sweet treat at the end. The food, kale and salmon salad and a steak were just right. I often struggle with restaurant food being too salty or too greasy for me. That was not the case here, our meal was light, fresh and very yummy. And I highly recommend fruit tart for desert too! We will be back.

Food is decadent but took forever to arrive: a full hour after we placed our order! Wait staff are professional and friendly. View of the marina is lovely. Worth the experience but prepare to spend some time and considerable money. And skip the filet - go for the fish.
Great mules, good food, will return. Reservations generally recommended at all hours. There is bar seating with full service. One of Marina del Rey's best!

Delicious, interesting seafood in a marina setting, Cafe del Rey was perfect. We weren't dressed for a fancy dinner, but in California that's fine. They took reservations and were gracious about our 7-year old being with us. We dined early at 5:30. As the evening progressed the clientele became much fancier, so we were glad we'd eaten early!

This is a great place to have a celebration, gatherings or meetings. This place is wonderful. You can sit indoors or outdoors overlooking the marina on a warm sunset night. Great atmosphere! Great service... Sunday champagne brunch was amazing. Great variety of food and good selection on the menu. The management staff caters to your needs. Vallet parking is $5.00. I love this place.

We ate simple here with a club sandwich and a kids quesadilla. Both were well prepared and served quickly. 

Their patio seating in back has a marina view but no foot traffic by the tables. In front they have a coy pond with some hungry fish.

I go salsa dancing here and they're really great! Very fun and active, nice atmosphere. Havent tried the food as I go for more social dance experience but seems like a great place to eat both for friends and romantic scene. Glad they are still around.

Very attentive waiting staff was refilling drinks before being asked. Parking was valet only since I believe they were painting the parking spot numbers at the time. I had the roast beef dip sandwich and garlic mashed potatoes which was very tasty.

The restaurant is 3.5 stars for food & service, ambience is 5 stars for sure. 

OTOH, the bar on this Saturday night was off the charts for live music with the Rick Whitfield Band. Even the First Lady of Folk, Joni Mitchell, was in the house and the band played Woodstock in tribute. Very cool!
